race.description: Coonabarabran Bowling Club Cup Day Sprint
race.comment: Solid contest with plenty of chances. ROUGE MOULIN (4) returned to form with a fast finishing second over 1200m at Coonamble in good time. Settles back in the field and a repeat of latest will see him go close. FEIRME PRINCE (3) slow into stride when up in trip and class for a plodding eighth over 1300m at Hawkesbury from the sticky gate. Clayton Gallagher goes aboard and his slashing placing two back had merit. ENTERPRISE LEGEND (7) smart country-trained sprinter who was a month between runs when coming to town for a fading eighth over 1000m at Warwick Farm in BM72 class. Good enough to play a leading role. SMART AND DAPPER (6) up in trip on the quick back-up when a fading fifth over 1200m at Coonamble. Since sent to the trials when a winner over 800m. Well in with the claim and not to be overlooked. DRIVING FORCE (1) indicated a win was imminent when he surged late to run third over 1200m at Coonamble. Goes into the exotics.
